data.name: Modified Hepburn
data.description: This is a modified version of Hepburn romanization, which was adopted by Kenkyusha's New Japanese-English Dictionary (3rd edition) One crucial difference between Modified and Tranditional Hepburn is that the ん/ン sound is always transliterated as n, even before the letters b,m,p.
